'''''Bacillus thuringiensis israelensis''''' ('''''Bti''''') is a group of bacteria used in [[biological control]]{{w|biological control}} of the larvae of certain insect pests. ''Bti'' is toxic to various species of mosquitoes and blackflies, yet has almost no effect on other organisms.{{fact}}

Bti is available commercially, both retail and in bulk for commercial and public agency use. It can come in liquid or granular form.

